title: Electron Auroral Images @ 1356A, Key Parameters, IMAGE Far UltraViolet (FUV) Spectrographic Imaging camera Electrons (SIE)  - S. Mende (UC/Berkeley/SSL)

parameters.name: SI_PIXELS
parameters.description: FUV/SIE Electron Images @ 1356A (raw cnts, no grid, small format, linear scaling) - use CDAWeb noise filter

parameters.name: SI_PIXELS_L
parameters.description: ---> As above (large format). This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function alternate_view (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['SI_PIXELS']. Note that not all COMPONENTS are time series and so their values are not available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.

parameters.name: SI_PIXELS_V
parameters.description: [DO NOT USE] FUV/SIE Electron Images @ 1356A (raw cnts, mapped, large format, linear scaling) - use CDAWeb noise filter. This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function alternate_view (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['SI_PIXELS', 'ORB_X', 'ORB_Y', 'ORB_Z']. Note that not all COMPONENTS are time series and so their values are not available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.

parameters.description: --->  [DO NOT USE] As above (movie format). This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function alternate_view (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['SI_PIXELS', 'ORB_X', 'ORB_Y', 'ORB_Z']. parameters.name: SI_PIXELS_LOG
parameters.description: FUV/SIE Electron Images @ 1356A (no grid, small format, log10 scaling). This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function convert_log10 (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['SI_PIXELS']. Note that not all COMPONENTS are time series and so their values are not available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.

parameters.name: SPIN
parameters.description: Spin number (time_equivalent)

parameters.name: DATA_QUAL
parameters.description: FUV/SIE Data Quality parameter (1=Good, 2=Bad)

parameters.name: RADIUS

parameters.name: HV

parameters.description: expansion factor for FOV

parameters.description: oriention direction cosine Z
